WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Hello, today we are going to talk about something that a lot of people are very sensitive about.

2
00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
That is, how do you evolve from the sense of frustration that you have when communicating with an AI teacher

3
00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.500
to the sense that you can cooperate with it?

4
00:00:10.500 --> 00:00:13.500
Are you ready to upgrade your AI skills together?

5
00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:15.500
OK, let's get started!

6
00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:17.500
You must have had this experience, right?

7
00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:23.000
That is, you think of a problem in your mind and send it out with full expectation.

8
00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:28.000
As a result, you jump out of the screen with a completely straight face,

9
00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.500
or even a cold, unsatisfied request like this.

10
00:00:32.500 --> 00:00:37.500
It's like you're talking to an AI, and then you hit a wall.

11
00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:39.500
It's really going to make people angry.

12
00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:43.500
So, how do you break the wall of communication?

13
00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:47.500
What should you do to become a partner who can really guide the AI and think with it

14
00:00:47.500 --> 00:00:52.500
from a user who can only give simple instructions?

15
00:00:52.500 --> 00:00:53.500
Don't worry.

16
00:00:53.500 --> 00:00:58.500
Today's content is going to give you a very clear and very structured roadmap.

17
00:00:58.500 --> 00:01:02.500
We basically have three steps for today.

18
00:01:02.500 --> 00:01:05.500
First, plan your AI journey.

19
00:01:05.500 --> 00:01:09.500
Then, create your own reminder toolbox.

20
00:01:09.500 --> 00:01:15.500
Finally, the most fun step is to practice through games.

21
00:01:15.500 --> 00:01:20.500
Follow these three steps, and you can step by step become an AI partner.

22
00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:22.500
Okay, let's start from the first step.

23
00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:25.500
Plan your AI journey.

24
00:01:25.500 --> 00:01:31.500
The key to this step is to help yourself build a system-based growth plan.

25
00:01:31.500 --> 00:01:36.500
This is not to blindly practice, but to strategically improve yourself,

26
00:01:36.500 --> 00:01:40.500
so that you can build a stable foundation for later progress.

27
00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:44.600
Now, let's take a look at this super useful self-evaluation tool.

28
00:01:44.600 --> 00:01:48.600
It covers the core capabilities of four cooperation with AI,

29
00:01:49.600 --> 00:01:51.600
which is to make the goal clear.

30
00:01:51.600 --> 00:01:55.600
Develop is to make your ideas better step by step.

31
00:01:55.600 --> 00:01:58.600
Direct is to give accurate instructions.

32
00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:03.600
And discern is to evaluate whether the AI is doing well.

33
00:02:03.600 --> 00:02:07.600
You can use this table to honestly evaluate yourself on these four projects.

34
00:02:07.600 --> 00:02:11.600
Are you a beginner? Are you still improving? Are you already very confident?

35
00:02:11.600 --> 00:02:15.600
Then, write down your strengths and where you need to strengthen.

36
00:02:15.600 --> 00:02:19.600
Do you know where you are now? Is it the first step of the planning route?

37
00:02:19.600 --> 00:02:24.820
Okay, after the evaluation, we come to the specific action plan.

38
00:02:24.820 --> 00:02:26.820
It's very simple, four steps.

39
00:02:26.820 --> 00:02:28.820
First, evaluate your current capabilities.

40
00:02:28.820 --> 00:02:35.820
Second, from those four capabilities, choose one or two goals that you think you need to strengthen the most.

41
00:02:35.820 --> 00:02:39.820
Then, plan specific practice activities and time tables.

42
00:02:39.820 --> 00:02:41.820
The most important step is coming.

43
00:02:41.820 --> 00:02:47.820
You need to have a very clear definition of how much progress and success you have made.

44
00:02:47.820 --> 00:02:51.820
In this way, your goal is no longer vague, I want to become strong,

45
00:02:51.820 --> 00:02:55.010
but a plan that can be carried out step by step.

46
00:02:55.010 --> 00:02:59.010
Okay, when you have drawn your own learning route,

47
00:02:59.010 --> 00:03:02.010
the next step is of course to prepare the equipment.

48
00:03:02.010 --> 00:03:04.010
So we come to the second stage,

49
00:03:04.010 --> 00:03:07.010
build your exclusive reminder toolbox.

50
00:03:07.010 --> 00:03:13.010
It's a little bit like preparing the most common things you usually do with the most effective tools.

51
00:03:13.010 --> 00:03:15.010
Let your efficiency fly straight.

52
00:03:15.010 --> 00:03:18.010
So, what is the reminder toolbox?

53
00:03:18.010 --> 00:03:23.010
It's a secret weapon toolbox that belongs to you.

54
00:03:23.010 --> 00:03:28.010
It contains the most effective reminder words that you can use directly,

55
00:03:28.010 --> 00:03:30.010
various good strategies,

56
00:03:30.010 --> 00:03:34.010
and those that you think AI has done very well.

57
00:03:34.010 --> 00:03:36.010
This is not just a copy and paste,

58
00:03:36.010 --> 00:03:40.010
this is the experience of working with AI.

59
00:03:40.010 --> 00:03:44.010
What should be in a good reminder toolbox?

60
00:03:44.010 --> 00:03:47.010
Well, you can start with these aspects.

61
00:03:47.010 --> 00:03:51.010
First, help you build some templates for the five to ten tasks you do most often.

62
00:03:51.010 --> 00:03:55.010
Write down what you think are the most useful description strategies.

63
00:03:55.010 --> 00:03:59.010
Also, how do you judge whether AI has done well?

64
00:03:59.010 --> 00:04:02.010
Record these identification models.

65
00:04:02.010 --> 00:04:06.010
Finally, collect some successful examples that you can refer to in the future.

66
00:04:06.010 --> 00:04:08.010
When you start building this toolbox,

67
00:04:08.010 --> 00:04:13.010
you will find that the quality of your communication with AI will really improve steadily.

68
00:04:13.010 --> 00:04:18.010
Well, the last stop of the journey is also the most interesting stop I think.

69
00:04:18.010 --> 00:04:20.010
Practice through games.

70
00:04:20.010 --> 00:04:23.010
Hey, don't underestimate this thing.

71
00:04:23.010 --> 00:04:25.010
It's not just fun.

72
00:04:25.010 --> 00:04:28.010
It's a great training ground.

73
00:04:29.010 --> 00:04:31.010
Let's take a look at an example.

74
00:04:31.010 --> 00:04:34.010
This is a game called exchange guessing games.

75
00:04:34.010 --> 00:04:36.010
On the left is a puzzle.

76
00:04:36.010 --> 00:04:40.010
I hit more than a hundred drums to draw out the sound of light.

77
00:04:40.010 --> 00:04:42.010
What am I doing?

78
00:04:42.010 --> 00:04:45.010
The answer is actually typing on a computer keyboard.

79
00:04:45.010 --> 00:04:47.010
But here's the point.

80
00:04:47.010 --> 00:04:48.010
Look at what's written on the right.

81
00:04:48.010 --> 00:04:51.010
The real goal is not to guess the correct answer by AI,

82
00:04:51.010 --> 00:04:54.010
but to analyze its reasoning process.

83
00:04:55.010 --> 00:04:57.010
When it guesses wrong,

84
00:04:57.010 --> 00:04:59.010
you don't just tell it the answer.

85
00:04:59.010 --> 00:05:02.010
Instead, you guide it to think.

86
00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:07.010
See if you can help it get back on the right track.

87
00:05:07.010 --> 00:05:10.010
Before we continue to play,

88
00:05:10.010 --> 00:05:15.010
let's pause and talk about a core skill that we are practicing.

89
00:05:15.010 --> 00:05:17.010
This word is very important.

90
00:05:17.010 --> 00:05:19.010
It's called identification.

91
00:05:19.010 --> 00:05:21.010
It's a very critical ability.

92
00:05:21.010 --> 00:05:27.010
It means that you have to be able to assess the production and thinking process of AI,

93
00:05:27.010 --> 00:05:30.010
and then guide the model to get a better result.

94
00:05:30.010 --> 00:05:32.010
To be honest,

95
00:05:32.010 --> 00:05:36.010
this is the biggest difference between professionals and ordinary users.

96
00:05:36.010 --> 00:05:40.080
This identification can be divided into three types.

97
00:05:40.080 --> 00:05:42.080
The first is result identification,

98
00:05:42.080 --> 00:05:46.080
which is to see if the answer given by AI is logical.

99
00:05:46.080 --> 00:05:48.080
The second is process identification,

100
00:05:48.080 --> 00:05:51.080
which is to see how AI came up with the answer,

101
00:05:51.080 --> 00:05:54.080
and what its thinking process is.

102
00:05:54.080 --> 00:05:57.080
The third is performance identification,

103
00:05:57.080 --> 00:06:01.080
which is to see if AI has made it clear.

104
00:06:01.080 --> 00:06:04.080
When you are playing a game or thinking,

105
00:06:04.080 --> 00:06:08.080
you can practice these three types of identification.

106
00:06:08.080 --> 00:06:09.080
Besides guessing,

107
00:06:09.080 --> 00:06:12.080
there are many other fun ways to practice.

108
00:06:12.080 --> 00:06:14.080
For example, 20 questions,

109
00:06:14.080 --> 00:06:16.080
how to tell a story,

110
00:06:16.080 --> 00:06:18.080
how to play a role,

111
00:06:18.080 --> 00:06:21.080
you can even give AI a very complex concept,

112
00:06:21.080 --> 00:06:25.080
but ask it to use super strict restrictions to explain.

113
00:06:25.080 --> 00:06:26.080
For example,

114
00:06:26.080 --> 00:06:28.080
you can only use main dishes to compare.

115
00:06:28.080 --> 00:06:32.080
These ways of playing to improve your communication skills are super helpful.

116
00:06:32.080 --> 00:06:36.080
I think this sentence is a great summary.

117
00:06:36.080 --> 00:06:39.080
The guidance skills learned in the game

118
00:06:39.080 --> 00:06:44.080
will be amazingly practical in real projects.

119
00:06:44.080 --> 00:06:45.080
This is the key.

120
00:06:45.080 --> 00:06:48.080
The skills you learn in the process of playing

121
00:06:48.080 --> 00:06:51.080
can be directly applied to your profession,

122
00:06:51.080 --> 00:06:54.080
or even on a very high-risk job.

123
00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:56.080
So, this is not a waste of time.

124
00:06:56.080 --> 00:06:59.080
You are making the most effective investment.

125
00:06:59.080 --> 00:07:04.080
So, AI is your new partner in thinking.

126
00:07:04.080 --> 00:07:06.080
After this journey from planning,

127
00:07:06.080 --> 00:07:10.080
to making tools, to real-life eye-catching,

128
00:07:10.080 --> 00:07:13.080
are you ready to lead this conversation?
